    "recap_headline": "University of Memphis Athletics",
    "recap_text": "MEMPHIS, Tenn. \u2013\nThe University of Memphis (4-12) baseball team picked up a 5-2 victory over Lipscomb (6-9) Tuesday afternoon at FedExPark Avron Fogelman Field.\nMemphis did most of its damage in the second inning, scoring four runs to take control of the game early. The Tigers added an insurance run in the seventh and relied on strong pitching out of the bullpen to secure the win.\nSeth Impson\nstarted on the mound for Memphis, allowing two runs across 4.1 innings before\nDavis Oswalt\ntook over in relief and earned the win with 2.2 scoreless innings.\nBrayden Sanders\nand\nCarson Fair\ncombined to close out the final two innings, with Fair recording his second save of the season.\nThe Tigers will remain at home for their next midweek matchup tomorrow when they host Arkansas-Pine Bluff at FedExPark Avron Fogelman Field. First pitch is scheduled for 4:05 p.m.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nMemphis broke through in the second inning after\nCade Hitson\ndrew a walk and\nJavon Hernandez\nsingled to put two runners on base.\nFreddy Rodriguez\ndelivered the big hit of the inning, lining a two-RBI single to left field that scored Hitson and Hernandez.\nAfter\nShane Cox\nreached on an infield single, a Lipscomb throwing error allowed Rodriguez and\nTrae Cassidy\nto score, giving the Tigers a 4-0 lead.\nLipscomb answered in the fourth inning when Blake Carter hit a two-run home run to left field to cut the Memphis lead to 4-2.\nThe Memphis bullpen took over in the fifth inning as\nDavis Oswalt\nentered and held the Bisons scoreless over the next 2.2 innings.\nIn the seventh,\nMarcus Smith\nadvanced to third on a throwing error before\nFreddy Rodriguez\ndrove him in on a fielder's choice to extend the lead to 5-2.\nBrayden Sanders\nworked a scoreless eighth inning and\nCarson Fair\nretired the side in order in the ninth to secure the Memphis victory.\nNOTABLES\nThird baseman\nFreddy Rodriguez\nled Memphis offensively, going 2-for-3 with three RBIs.\nThis marks his sixth multi-hit game of the season as well as his fourth game with multiple RBIs.\nHis three RBIs are a season high.\nDavis Oswalt\nearned his first win of the season with 2.2 scoreless innings in relief.\nCarson Fair\npicked up his second save of the season after pitching a scoreless ninth inning.\nMemphis pitching combined to hold Lipscomb to six hits in the contest.\nThe six hits are tied for the least amount given up in any game this season.\nAfter another hit Tuesday, second baseman\nShane Cox\ncontinued his streak of reaching base safely in every game thus far and continues his nine-game hitting streak.\nCox leads the Tigers in batting average (.382), hits (26), doubles (6), and extra-base hits (9).\nSCORING SUMMARY\nBottom 2:\nFreddy Rodriguez\nsingled,\nCade Hitson\nand\nJavon Hernandez\nscored.\nFreddy Rodriguez\nand\nTrae Cassidy\nscored on a throwing error.\nMemphis 4, Lipscomb 0\nTop 4:\nBlake Carter homered, Keaton Mahan scored.\nMemphis 4, Lipscomb 2\nBottom 7:\nFreddy Rodriguez\nreached on a fielder's choice,\nMarcus Smith\nscored.\nMemphis 5, Lipscomb 2\nUP NEXT\nMemphis will continue its homestand Wednesday afternoon against Arkansas-Pine Bluff at FedExPark Avron Fogelman Field. First pitch is scheduled for 4:05 p.m.\nHOW TO FOLLOW THE TIGERS:\nFor complete information on\u00a0Memphis Tiger Baseball, visit\nwww.GoTigersGo.com\nand follow the team's social media channels on\nTwitter\n,\nInstagram\nand\nFacebook\n."
